
 Usage

The meshgrid function generates arrays that can be used for
the generation of surface plots. The syntax is one of

    [X,Y] = meshgrid(x)
    [X,Y] = meshgrid(x,y)
    [X,Y,Z] = meshgrid(x,y,z)

where x,y,z are vectors, and X,Y,Z are matrices. In the
first case [X,Y] = meshgrid(x), the rows of X and the
columns of Y contain copies of the vector x. In the second
case [X,Y] = meshgrid(x,y), the rows of X contain copies of
x, and the columns of Y contain copies of y. In the third
case, each input is copied along the row, column or slice
direction of the corresponding output variable.


